subSubSection.paragraph:
Palp
: tibial apophysis with 4 stouter spines, and several strong spines on subterminal ledge (Fig. 
4A-C
); paracymbium with many short strong setae situated at the tip (Fig. 
4B, C
); cumulus distinctly elevated with several spines on tip (Fig. 
4C
); subtegular apophysis large, strongly developed (Fig. 
4D, F
); proximal edge of contrategulum elevated (Fig. 
4F, G
); tegulum lunate, with dentate margin (Fig. 
4G
); embolic parts adjoining (Fig. 
4E, F, G
); embolus with 2 longitudinal ridges reaching the tip distally (Fig. 
4D, E, G
).
